_header: As I forth walketh airily among the goves and pleasant springs
_description: Song, or ballad, surviving in fragmentary form only — two or three lines

YorkMinBarton.Transcription:
As I forth walkeeth aireley among the groves and pleasant springsin
                    the maerie moneth of Maye…
YorkMinBarton.Note:
Follows 2714, numbered
                    26 in what must have originally been a book of ballads.
